  const parsed = idSchema.safeParse(req.params.id);
  if (!parsed.success) return res.status(400).json({ error: 'Invalid id' });
  // ... use parsed.data
});
```

Also add `express.json({ limit: '100kb' })` **with a size cap** before any body-parsing route, so oversized payloads can't exhaust memory.

## 3. Security Headers & Hardening

Currently no headers, no rate limiting, no CORS policy.

