if (require.main === module) {
  app.listen(PORT, () => console.log(`listening on ${PORT}`));
}
module.exports = app;
```

## 8. Logging leaks / lack of structure

`console.log` is fine for dev, but swap for a structured logger (`pino`, `winston`) with request IDs and redaction of sensitive fields (`authorization`, `cookie`, `email`). Never log request bodies unconditionally.

## 9. Graceful shutdown

Handle `SIGTERM`/`SIGINT` so in-flight requests complete and sockets close cleanly — important behind orchestrators (Kubernetes, ECS):

```js
